&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I am not so sure on the concerns quoted above. I'll have to look at the AC of monks now a days... but half the problem that was there before was also created by itemization, like 50 ac pants from Avatar of War.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Since then I beleive that the gear for monks has dropped in AC substantially, though I may be wrong.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Can anyone shed light here?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The nerf was brought about for one reason because at the time there was an AC hard cap.&amp;nbsp; I can't remember the exact numbers right off but I think it was a little above 1k AC.&amp;nbsp; If any class went over the hard cap it didn't do anything to their damage taking ability.&amp;nbsp; So at the time a 1200 AC monk would mitigate the same as a 1500 AC warrior since both were above the hard cap.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The AC system has since been changed.&amp;nbsp; Today there are soft caps, which has been parsed at 1340ish for monks.&amp;nbsp; Once the soft cap has been reached there is a diminished return on AC above it.&amp;nbsp; And it is true that the AC items available to monks today are not as close to what the plate classes can acheive as it was pre nerf.&amp;nbsp; So the monks ability to generate AC is still going to be below the plate classes.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
